Oauth2 - is a protocol to provide temporary access to a resource
..... 

webserver flow
..............

Ex:- user -> app (our app asking to login with google)

User login with google - and get grant(code)

and provide that grant to server which he requesting to access

and with that grant-temperory, server(app) will communicate with google to get access token

with that access token server will communicate Google resource server to get details

IdAnywhere - ia  a thin layer built top on oauth2 for login
........... 

